f016ed2 : Defer resizes if Idle thread is not running (#3271)
Sat, 28 Nov 2020 08:42:48 -0500
Paul

Defer resizes if Idle thread is not running (#3271)

If the idle thread has never run in the VST3, don't call
resize but instead queue up the resize for the first idle.
This allows hosts which have not finisihed initialization
fully to still call the resize codepath as written.

Specifically Bitwig 3.1.2 hangs when you start it with current. I think it
is because the first resize is before the iPlugFrame is fully
initialized. So push the resize to the idle loop instead.

Closes #3270